    slug: "namaz-se-pehle-new-edition",
    description: `Namaz Se Pehle (New Edition) is an updated and revised Urdu-language book that focuses on the essential preparations, conditions, and recommended acts that a Muslim should observe before performing the five daily prayers, ensuring that each prayer is offered in the best possible manner and with the greatest spiritual benefit. This new edition has been carefully reviewed and expanded to include additional content, improved organisation, and clearer presentation of the material based on feedback from readers and scholars. The book begins by explaining the prerequisites (shurut) of Salah, covering the conditions that must be fulfilled before the prayer can even begin, including ritual purity through wudu (ablution) or ghusl (bathing), cleanliness of the body and clothing, covering of the awrah (nakedness), facing the qiblah, and being at the proper time for the prayer. Each condition is explained in detail with reference to the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations, so the reader understands not only what is required but why it matters. The section on the adhan (call to prayer) and iqamah covers their significance, the proper method of calling them, the supplications recommended after hearing them, and the importance of proceeding promptly to the mosque after the iqamah. A substantial portion of the book is devoted to the sunnah acts and recommended preparations before prayer, including the performance of the rawatib (regular sunnah prayers) that precede the obligatory prayers, the supplication before entering the mosque, the two rak'ahs of tahiyyat al-masjid (greeting the mosque), the recommended du'as while waiting for the congregational prayer to begin, and the importance of straightening the rows and filling the gaps. The book also addresses the spiritual preparation for prayer, discussing the importance of approaching Salah with a calm and focused mind, clearing the heart of worldly distractions, and recalling the majesty of the One before whom the worshipper is about to stand. The new edition includes additional chapters on topics that were not covered in the previous version, such as dealing with waswas (whispers in prayer), overcoming forgetfulness and laziness regarding prayer, and creating a prayer-friendly environment in the home. Practical tips are provided for families, including how to encourage children to pray and how to establish a consistent prayer routine in a busy household. Written in clear and accessible Urdu, this revised edition is a valuable resource for both new Muslims learning the basics of prayer preparation and experienced worshippers seeking to enhance the quality of their daily Salah.`,
