    slug: "namaz-e-nabvi-hisn-ul-muslim-14x21",
    description: `Namaz-e-Nabvi and Hisn-ul-Muslim 14x21 is a combined edition Urdu-language Islamic reference book that brings together two essential works in a single, conveniently sized 14x21 centimetre volume. The first section of this compilation presents a detailed guide to Namaz-e-Nabvi (the Prophetic Prayer), covering the complete method of performing the five daily prayers exactly as Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) performed them, based exclusively on authentic hadith narrations. This section covers the prerequisites of prayer, the intention, the opening takbir, the recitation, the ruku, the sujud, the tashahhud, the salawat upon the Prophet, and the concluding salam, with each step accompanied by the relevant supplications in Arabic with Urdu translation. The second section contains Hisn-ul-Muslim (Fortress of the Muslim), one of the most widely used and trusted collections of daily supplications (azkar) in the Muslim world. This section organises the authentic supplications from the Quran and Sunnah by occasion and time, covering the morning and evening adhkar, supplications for before and after eating, du'as for sleeping and waking, prayers for travelling, supplications for entering and leaving the mosque, du'as for wearing new clothes, prayers during illness, supplications for seeking forgiveness, du'as for various life situations, and many other categories that cover the complete range of a Muslim's daily spiritual practice. Each supplication is presented with its Arabic text, Urdu translation, and reference to the source hadith, allowing readers to verify its authenticity. The 14x21 centimetre format strikes an ideal balance between portability and readability, making this combined volume suitable for use at home, in the mosque, at the workplace, or while travelling. The durable binding ensures that the book can withstand regular daily use without the pages becoming loose. By combining the prayer guide with the comprehensive supplication collection, this edition eliminates the need to carry two separate books, making it an especially practical resource for Muslims who wish to maintain a consistent practice of both Salah and daily azkar. The clear formatting and logical organisation make it easy to quickly find any supplication or prayer instruction, and the compact size ensures it fits comfortably in most bags and purses. This dual-purpose reference is an essential addition to every Muslim household and an excellent gift for new Muslims, students, and anyone seeking to strengthen their daily practice of Islam.`,
